long_desc.thetext:
This code is a bit bizarre, but Exchange#wasSuccessful() is given a status code of -1 if an attempt to retrieve the status from a request throws an error:

    getStatusCode : function()
    {
      var vStatusCode = -1;

      try {
        vStatusCode = this.getRequest().status;
      } catch(ex) {}

      return vStatusCode;
    },

This would indicate to me that either there's a bug (getRequest() returns null because there's no request in progress) or the request has no status member (very strange).

The comment in wasSuccessful should probably say, "Status code was not available", but why that's OK for various MSXML versions I have no idea.

(A complete rewrite of qx.io.remote such that it's readable and better organized would be a really nice project for someone with good networking experience who's looking to contribute to qooxdoo!)

